INSERT INTO `wp_ricpsi_posts` VALUES (150, 5, '2013-08-30 22:31:32', '2013-08-30 22:31:32', 'The following is a template for the toolkits, a live brainstorm of essential elements that will be useful for members of the community that would like to contribute to it\'s development.\n\n<strong>Basics of CC</strong>\n\n<a href="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/video_icono1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-76" alt="video_icono" src="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/video_icono1.png" width="54" height="52" /></a> <strong></strong>\n\n- The following video from CC Qatar shows how Creative Commons works:\n[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_P-bQB8zUSo&amp;w=560&amp;h=315]\n\n- This other video shows how Creative Commons licences can help you to download and share digital content legally:\n[vimeo 25684782 w=500 h=281]\n\n<a href="http://vimeo.com/25684782">Creative Commons Kiwi</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/ccanz">CreativeCommons AotearoaNZ</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.\n\n<a href="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hoja_icono1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-77" alt="hoja_icono" src="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hoja_icono1.png" width="51" height="50" /></a>\n\n- http://wiki.creativecommons.org/images/6/62/Creativecommons-informational-flyer_eng.pdf\n\n- This Open <a href="http://creativecommons.pl/2012/06/open-poster-about-cc-licenses/">Poster</a> about CC licenses was published by Creative Commons Poland. It was designed by <a href="http://www.piotrekchuchla.com/">Piotrek Chuchla</a>, graphic designer and poster artist and is downloadable in PDF and open SVG formats for print, remix and next translations. Download it in <a href="http://creativecommons.pl/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/CC_licencje_plakat_ENG_A2.pdf">A2 format (PDF)</a>, <a href="http://creativecommons.pl/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/CC_licencje_plakat_ENG_B1.pdf">B1 (PDF)</a> and <a href="http://creativecommons.pl/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/vector_wektory_cc_poster3.zip">open vectors package (poster and all used icons)</a>.\n\n- <a href="http://creativecommons.org.au/content/What_is_CC_edu.pdf">Here</a> you can find a CC guide jointly developed by the ARC Centre of Excellence for Creative Industries and Innovation through Creative Commons Australia and the Copyright Advisory Group of the Ministerial Council of Education, Employment, Training and Youth Affairs.\n\n- <a href="http://creativecommons.org.au/content/Quick-Reference-Guide-to-Finding-Creative-Commons-Material.doc">A Quick Reference Guide to Finding Creative Commons Material</a>\n\n<a href="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/diapos_icono.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-85" alt="diapos_icono" src="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/diapos_icono.png" width="53" height="52" /></a>\n\n- <a href="http://wiki.creativecommons.org/Sharing_Creative_Works_0" target="_blank">Sharing Creative Works</a> is a new comic about CC. It aims to explain the basics of CC licensing as simply as possible to a general audience, including children. To make remixes and translations as easy as possible, the original artwork is in SVG format and all the assets are available for <a href="http://mirrors.creativecommons.org/comics/sharingcreativeworks/sharingcreativeworks.zip">download</a>. Please contribute!', 'Template_old', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'template_old', '', '', '2013-08-30 22:31:32', '2013-08-30 22:31:32', '', 0, 'http://cctoolkits.wordpress.com/?page_id=150', 0, 'page', '', 0) ; 
