awecka">Dorota Kawƒôcka</a></td>\r\n<td width="50%";><img class="alignleft" src="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/alek_portret_avatar.jpg" alt="" width="73" height="73" /> <a href="https://twitter.com/atarkowski">Alek Tarkowski</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Translation</h3>\r\n<table border="0"; style="border-collapse:collapse;" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="50%";><img class="alignleft" src="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/kayode_avatar.png" alt="" width="73" height="73" /> <a href="https://twitter.com/k_whybaba">Kayode Yussuf</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nFor more information about working group leads and contact information, see <a href="http://wiki.creativecommons.org/Toolkits">wiki.creativecommons.org/Toolkits</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<small><a href="http://thenounproject.com/noun/team/#icon-No8501">Team</a> icon by Bj√∂rn Andersson, from The Noun Project</small>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '236-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-18 00:05:44', '2014-07-18 00:05:44', '', 236, 'http://cctoolkits.com/236-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_ricpsi_posts` VALUES (421, 5, '2013-12-12 20:06:05', '2013-12-12 20:06:05', '<img class=" wp-image-75 alignleft" alt="icon_checkmark" src="http://cctoolkits.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/icon_checkmark.png?w=150" width="80" height="80" />The aim of this project is to construct toolkits of openly licensed digital resources so that others can learn and share about the importance of CC in sectors of global society.\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>We\'re building toolkits together.</strong></h3>\r\nThese content bundles (toolkits, for short) will source OERs about Education, Science, Government, Creative Industries, and other areas that are key to broadening the Commons. The toolkits will be available for free on the web, fully CC-licensed and remixable, and will include pieces such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Video clips</li>\r\n	<li>Presentation slides</li>\r\n	<li>1-Page outlines of the benefits of CC</li>\r\n	<li>Answers to frequently asked questions (FAQ)</li>\r\n	<li>Case studies and use cases</li>\r\n	<li>Printable cards and handouts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe presentation (below) from the CC Global Summit explains the basic concept of the toolkit project: CC affiliates to work on teams in development sprints at events around the globe. For more information, see <a href="http://wiki.creativecommons.org/Toolkits">wiki.creativecommons.org/Toolkits</a>\r\n\r\n<iframe src="//slid.es/billymeinke/toolkits/embed?style=light" width="576" height="420" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<small><a href="http://thenounproject.com/noun/check-mark/#icon-No17641">Check Mark</a> icon by Erin Standley, from The Noun Project</small>', 'Objective', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-12 20:06:05', '2013-12-12 20:06:05', '', 15, 'http://cctoolkits.com/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
